title: Aretha Franklin - Jewels In The Crown
description:
Browse the assembled talent on this disc and you&#039;re bound to be wowed by the bold names--Hello, Frank Sinatra, George Benson, and Elton John--but anyone who&#039;s been listening to the Queen of Soul long enough knows even fellow legends often have cause to feel humbled in her presence. And it&#039;s interesting, but the duets collected here tend to work in inverse proportion to the fame of the collaborator: "Hello My Love" with Sinatra is so-so, though it&#039;s certainly not for lack of effort by the always-on Aretha, while "Put You Up on Game" with American Idol&#039;s Fantasia comes as a revelation; Fantasia could have been all crack-voiced and quaking in her spike-heeled ankle boots, but she proves up to the challenge. If the heavy hitters were cowed by the Queen&#039;s supremacy and it shows (it does), it&#039;s worth remembering that a lot of the recycled tracks here--the ones you&#039;ll most likely buy the record for, including the exceptional "Sisters Are Doin&#039; It for Themselves" with the Eurythmics and "I Knew You Were Waiting (For Me)" with George Michael--more than make up for it. Also, three new duets--the one with Fantasia, plus one with John Legend, and one with Mary J. Blige--prove Aretha&#039;s becoming more selective with her singing partners.
